	<h2>Why I Built Conduital</h2>

	<p>
		I'm Greg Maxfield — a knowledge worker, writer, and systems thinker
		based in Utah. I've spent years trying to make productivity tools
		work the way my brain actually works. I tried paper planners, Todoist,
		Trello, Obsidian, and more Notion templates than I can count. Every one
		of them started strong and faded within two weeks — not because I lacked
		discipline, but because the tools demanded more maintenance than they
		gave back.
	</p>

	<p>
		Conduital grew out of that frustration. I wanted a system built on
		Notion's flexibility, but with the intelligence to maintain itself —
		one that tracks momentum instead of just task completion, surfaces
		what matters instead of burying it in databases, and adapts when
		priorities shift (which they always do).
	</p>

	<h2>What Makes This Different</h2>

	<p>
		Most productivity templates are containers. You put things in; you
		take things out. The organizational work is entirely on you. Conduital
		is different because it does cognitive work for you:
	</p>

	<ul>
		<li><strong>Momentum tracking</strong> — not just "done or not done," but a living score that shows whether each project is moving, stalling, or needs attention.</li>
		<li><strong>AI-powered reviews</strong> — a weekly review co-pilot that summarizes your portfolio, flags risks, and suggests where to focus next.</li>
		<li><strong>Automatic discovery</strong> — Conduital watches your file system and surfaces new projects, areas, and resources as they appear. No manual entry required.</li>
		<li><strong>GTD meets PARA</strong> — the system bridges David Allen's Getting Things Done methodology with Tiago Forte's PARA framework, giving you both the action clarity of GTD and the organizational depth of a second brain.</li>
	</ul>

	<h2>Who It's For</h2>

	<p>
		Conduital is built for knowledge workers, freelancers, and solopreneurs
		who manage a mix of creative projects, ongoing responsibilities, and
		long-term goals. If you've ever felt like you're spending more time
		organizing your system than doing actual work, this is for you.
	</p>

	<p>
		It's not for people who want the simplest possible to-do list — there
		are great tools for that. It's for people whose work is complex enough
		that they need a real system, but who are tired of being the full-time
		maintenance crew for that system.
	</p>

	<h2>The Company</h2>

	<p>
		Conduital is a product of <strong>Silver Sage, LLC</strong>. It's an
		independent, bootstrapped project — no venture funding, no growth-at-all-costs
		pressure. That means every design decision serves the people who use it,
		not an investor deck.
	</p>

	<p>
